description: Ancient Greek ὀνειροκριτικός (oneirokritikós) (from ὄνειρος (óneiros, “dream”) + κριτικός (kritikós, “able to discern”))  +‎ -al.

adjectives.description: oneirocritical (comparative more oneirocritical, superlative most oneirocritical)

entries.meaning: Of or relating to the interpretation of dreams.
examples: he may employ himself a while in that new kind of observation which my oneirocritical correspondent has directed him to make of himself.
